Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Joshua Wood

2023-03-12

My meme

I went onto cat images looking for inspiration and saw a hungry looking tiger, the meme quickly followed.

library(magick)

#creating images of the tiger to use in the meme

tiger_1 <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2018/01/21/09/56/tiger-3096211_960_720.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "??",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 gravity = "south")

tiger_2 <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2016/11/29/10/07/tiger-1868911_960_720.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "mmmm",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 gravity = "south")


# creating images of meals for the tiger

veg_image <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2016/03/05/19/02/appetite-1238251_960_720.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(400)

fish_image <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2015/04/08/13/13/food-712665_960_720.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(400)

# creating the rows of the meme

top_row <- image_append(c(tiger_1, veg_image))

middle_row <- image_append(c(tiger_2, fish_image))

# construction of meme

meme <- image_append(c(top_row, middle_row),stack = TRUE)

# saving meme

image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

I saw that I needed 4 frames and noted that 3 of them could be used to count down to the 4th frame, since I had cat images open and no other inspiration so I used that image.

library(magick)

# Creation of five frames

frame_1 <- image_blank(width = 400,
                       height = 400,
                       color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Cat in",
                 color = "#EE00FF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "North") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "3",
                 color = "#EE00FF",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "Center")

frame_2 <- image_blank(width = 400,
                       height = 400,
                       color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Cat in",
                 color = "#EE00FF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "North") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "2",
                 color = "#EE00FF",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "Center")

frame_3 <- image_blank(width = 400,
                       height = 400,
                       color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Cat in",
                 color = "#EE00FF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "North") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "1",
                 color = "#EE00FF",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "Center")

frame_4 <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2014/03/29/09/17/cat-300572__340.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(400)

# animating images

animation <- image_animate(c(frame_1, frame_2, frame_3, frame_4),fps = 2)

image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
